Sorry — I don’t have access to a "time" tool in this environment, so I can’t check the clock automatically.

If you tell me a timezone or city (or your current local time), I can convert or compute times for you. Or I can show quick ways to check the time on your device (e.g., Windows: open cmd and run "time /T"; macOS/Linux: open Terminal and run "date"). Which would you prefer?
